def: A rope to haul down, or to assist in hauling down, a sail; as,a staysail downhaul; a trysail downhaul.
A garden plant (Chrysanthemum Balsamita) having a strongbalsamic smell, and nearly allied to tansy. It is used as a pot herband salad plant and in flavoring ale and beer. Called also alecost.
The Marxian socialism and programme of reform throughrevolution as advocated by the French political leader Jules BasileGuesde (pron. ged) (1845- ). -- Guesd"ist (#), n. & a.
An instrument for regulating the electro-motive force in analternating-current circuit; -- so called because used to "boost", orraise, the pressure in the circuit.
Any one of numerous species of moths of the family Zygænidæ,most of which are bright colored. The wood nymph and the vineforester are examples. Also used adjectively.
A spring or mineral water; -- so called from a place of thisname in Belgium.
Holland gin made at Schiedam in the Netherlands.
On board; into or within a ship or boat; hence, into or withina railway car.
A way along which something slides.
Furnished with a virole or viroles; -- said of a horn or abugle when the rings are of different tincture from the rest of thehorn.
